The paper discusses techniques for learning representations from multiple views of data, which is a common problem in machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on deep neural network-based approaches and evaluates them on image, speech, and text tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper discusses optimization procedures and performance trade-offs, which could also place it in cs.SD (Software Engineering) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
